      src="http://static1.squarespace.com/static/5360d035e4b0ec04b0fdcce6/t/553663aee4b0819833f2fbf0/1430284270749/?format=1500w"
      width="200" /> </blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">Romeâ€™s enduring contribution to world civilization can, and should, be
      communicated in a way that combines the hard facts, solid reasoning, and new discoveries of
      university research with the excitement and immediacy of on-location filming in Rome. If a
      picture is worth a thousand words, then a video is worth a million.<br /><br
      />Ancient Rome Live (ARL) is an immersive journey that provides new perspectives about the
      ancient city. A multi-platform learning experience, ARL first and foremost presents
      <em>original</em> content:</span><br /><ul
      dir="ltr"><li><span style="font-size: x-small;">a clickable map of ancient
      Rome</span></li><li><span style="font-size: x-small;">a library of
      videos arranged according to topic</span></li><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">live streaming from sites in Rome and her
      empire.</span></li></ul><span style="font-size: x-small;">ARL provides
      an interactive platform to engage the many layers of Rome: monuments, people, places, and
      events.&nbsp; Ancient Rome Live&nbsp; is a valuable resource for teachers- and a lot of
      fun for anyone interested in history.<br /><br />Later in 2015 ARL will release an
      ebook, app, and free online course.&nbsp;&nbsp; WIth all of these new, coordinated
      formats, ARL will change the way ancient Rome is studied.<br /><br
